Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.17,0:19:29.14,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Just like me.{\r}\N就像现在的我一样
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.93,0:19:34.74,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}She was going to become a famous artist,but then she got sick.{\r}\N她本来可以成为一名著名的艺术家的 但是她生了病
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.05,0:19:37.41,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'm glad my mom never gets sick.{\r}\N我很庆幸我妈妈从来没生过病
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.41,0:19:39.38,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I don't know what I'd do without her.{\r}\N要是没有她我都不知道该怎么办好
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.57,0:19:46.77,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Aoise, come back here. You're supposed to be modeling for me.{\r}\N阿洛伊斯 快回来 你不是给我当模特的吗
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.25,0:19:52.40,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Well, models are supposed to get paid,you know.{\r}\N可是 模特是要讲报酬的 对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.46,0:19:54.89,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Not if they don't sit still.{\r}\N要是乱动的话就没有啦
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.85,0:20:01.06,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Aloise, sit...{\r}\N阿洛伊斯 坐...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.33,0:20:26.35,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Thank you, William. It's wonderful.{\r}\N真谢谢你 威廉大叔 这太棒了
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.63,0:20:29.28,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Such soft leather.{\r}\N这皮多软啊
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.28,0:20:31.84,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Where did you get it? - Where'd you get it, William?{\r}\N-你从哪里弄到的啊? -这块皮革是从哪里来的啊 威廉大叔
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.80,0:20:35.76,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Your apron! - Oh, no!{\r}\N-你的围裙! -噢 不!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.60,0:20:43.19,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Look at your faces!What have you been doing?{\r}\N看看你们的小脏脸儿! 你们都干什么去了?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.19,0:20:45.42,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Your father will blame me for sure.{\r}\N你爸爸肯定要怪我了
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.18,0:20:48.52,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Aloise, your mother's been looking for you.{\r}\N阿洛伊斯 你妈妈正找你呢
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.65,0:20:51.00,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Coming, Papa.{\r}\N就来 爸爸
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.68,0:20:56.89,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Look at you.Who's been painting your face?{\r}\N瞧瞧你 谁把你画成了大花脸啊?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.89,0:20:59.84,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Hello, Master Cogez. - Nello, William.{\r}\N-你好 库格兹先生 -尼洛 威廉
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.50,0:21:02.38,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Say, "Bye-bye, Nello. " -Bye-bye, Nello.{\r}\N-说 "再见 尼洛" -再见 尼洛
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.38,0:21:04.66,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Say, "Bye-bye, William. " - Bye-bye, William.{\r}\N-说 "再见 威廉叔叔" -再见 威廉叔叔
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.23,0:21:06.76,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Bye-bye - Bye, Aloise{\r}\N-再见 -再见 阿洛伊斯
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.95,0:21:08.28,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Oh, look at you.{\r}\N瞧瞧你
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.34,0:21:11.44,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Lucky man, Baas Cogez, huh?{\r}\N巴斯·库格兹真是个幸运的人 对吧?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.57,0:21:16.26,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Oh look, you and Patrasche get that milk to town before you lose your customers.{\r}\N你和帕奇快点送牛奶到镇子上去 不然人家下次就不订你的牛奶了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.26,0:21:17.53,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Clean your face on the way.{\r}\N在路上记得把脸洗干净
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.30,0:21:20.21,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Thank you, William. - All right.{\r}\N-谢谢你 威廉大叔 -没事的 去吧
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.41,0:21:57.84,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Children! Children! Sit down. - Hi, Aloise.{\r}\N-孩子们!孩子们! 坐下 -嗨 阿洛伊斯
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.34,0:22:12.39,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}There's a great painting inside that cathedral.{\r}\N在那个大教堂有一幅很棒的画
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.59,0:22:15.44,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Grandpa says Mother once saw it.{\r}\N爷爷说妈妈曾经见过它
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.67,0:22:19.06,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Wish I could see it too.{\r}\N我也想去看看
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.87,0:22:49.70,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Are you an admirer of Rubens as well?{\r}\N你也很崇拜鲁本斯吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.22,0:22:51.97,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Yes, sir. He's my hero.{\r}\N是的 先生 他是我的英雄
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.97,0:22:56.02,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'm sure the great master is happy to see bright new eyes looking up at him.{\r}\N我肯定这位大师 看到有这样一双年轻明亮的眼睛注视着他会很开心的
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.02,0:22:57.10,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I want to meet him.{\r}\N我想见见他
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.37,0:23:01.08,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Rubens passed away many years ago.{\r}\N鲁本斯许多年前就去世了
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.67,0:23:03.21,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Of course, his art lives on.{\r}\N当然 他的艺术还流传在世间
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.78,0:23:07.94,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Great men and their deeds always do live on.{\r}\N伟人和他们的事迹总会流芳百世的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.87,0:23:10.35,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And that's a comfort.{\r}\N而这也算是一种告慰吧
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.73,0:23:20.78,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Please, sir.{\r}\N请等一下先生
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.16,0:23:25.02,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Tell me more. I want to become a great artist too.{\r}\N能不能再跟我说说 我也想成为一个伟大的艺术家
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.33,0:23:26.50,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Oh, you do?{\r}\N噢 真的吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.12,0:23:30.10,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Well, you've made a proper start.{\r}\N好吧 你开了个好头
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.34,0:23:33.17,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Rubens was a master of every aspect of art.{\r}\N鲁本斯在艺术的各个方面都是大师级别的存在
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.80,0:23:35.32,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Composition, light{\r}\N构图 光线
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.44,0:23:37.29,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}movement.{\r}\N动作
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.00,0:23:41.94,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But he had to study.He studied down there, around the corner.{\r}\N但是他也得学习 就在那里 街道转角的附近
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.33,0:23:45.97,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Right here in this city? - He was a great teacher as well.{\r}\N-就在这座城里吗? -他也曾是个伟大的老师
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.97,0:23:50.23,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But what made him really great was that he was interested...{\r}\N但是真正让他变得伟大的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.23,0:23:52.33,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}was interested and excited about everything.{\r}\N是他对任何事情都充满着兴趣与激情
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.86,0:23:53.86,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'm like that.{\r}\N我就是这样的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.54,0:23:56.69,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'm sure you are.{\r}\N我也相信你一定是的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.36,0:23:58.27,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Michel!{\r}\N米歇尔!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.97,0:24:00.68,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Milk?{\r}\N牛奶?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.41,0:24:05.29,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Artists of our caliber should only drink cognac.{\r}\N我们这种级别的艺术家应该喝的是白兰地吧
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.56,0:24:08.80,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Let's see what these characters are up to, shall we?{\r}\N我们去会会那些人吧 怎么样?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.00,0:24:13.13,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Robert Kessler{\r}\N罗伯特·凯斯勒
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.73,0:24:17.36,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}may I present Master Michel La Grande.{\r}\N请允许我向你介绍米歇尔·拉格兰德大师
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.00,0:24:21.06,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I've studied your painting in the town hall, sir.{\r}\N我在市政厅学习过您的画作 先生
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.40,0:24:25.76,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I believe you know his father,our esteemed mayor.{\r}\N我想你一定认识他的父亲 也就是我们敬爱的市长
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.22,0:24:27.04,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Of course.{\r}\N当然
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.36,0:24:30.56,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Robert's been studying in London's Royal Conservatory of Art.{\r}\N罗伯特最近在伦敦皇家音乐学院学习艺术
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.49,0:24:34.35,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}As you can see, he has a lot of potential.{\r}\N如你所见 他很有潜能
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.35,0:24:36.58,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You always had an eye for potential.{\r}\N你总是有一双慧眼
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.33,0:24:41.74,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}-Let me introduce you to my friend...Nello{\r}\N-让我来介绍一下我的朋友...尼洛
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.21,0:24:44.04,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Master Steerns. Robert.{\r}\N这位是斯蒂恩斯大师 这是罗伯特
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.76,0:24:48.24,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}That's right I don't suppose I know his father.Do I?{\r}\N我想我应该不认识他的父亲吧 对吗
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.50,0:24:50.87,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Dietrich, please.{\r}\N迪特里克 请注意你的身份
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.59,0:24:52.48,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Yes, well...{\r}\N哦 好...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.90,0:24:58.65,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I was prepared to show Robert Rubens'greatest work, if you care to join us.{\r}\N我准备带罗伯特看看鲁本斯最伟大的画作 不介意的话就一起吧
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.09,0:25:02.49,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I was just on my way,with my friend, Nello.{\r}\N我和我的朋友尼洛马上就来
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.67,0:25:04.96,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Can Patrasche come too?{\r}\N帕奇也能一起进去吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.46,0:25:09.25,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}The priest doesn't allow dogs.{\r}\N那些牧师们是不会让狗进入的
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.67,0:25:12.09,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}He barely tolerates humans unless they have...{\r}\N他们也就只能容忍一些...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.72,0:25:13.53,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}potential.{\r}\N有潜力的人
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.52,0:25:18.18,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- So tie up your friend and then join us. - Okay.{\r}\N-把你的朋友安置好然后和我们一起进去吧 -好的
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.85,0:25:20.23,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Come, Patrasche.{\r}\N过来 帕奇
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.70,0:25:27.62,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Michel, I'm starting a little salon on Tuesdays.{\r}\N米歇尔 星期二我会办一个展览
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.62,0:25:28.95,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You should drop by for schnapps.{\r}\N你真的应该过来喝一杯
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.36,0:25:31.70,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'm afraid I'll be busy for the next...{\r}\N我想我最近...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.62,0:25:34.08,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}four or five years.{\r}\N四五年内都会很忙
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.64,0:25:39.73,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}That, my boy, is what we call a brushoff.{\r}\N我的孩子 这就是我们所说的拒绝
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.73,0:25:43.81,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Not at all. I'm going off to Rome to paint some murals.{\r}\N不 不是的 我要去罗马画壁画
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.20,0:25:47.36,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}A new commission from the Church.{\r}\N教堂指派的新任务
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.66,0:25:49.41,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Really?{\r}\N真的吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.27,0:25:52.53,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Does his Holiness pay well?{\r}\N教皇陛下舍得给钱吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.53,0:25:56.22,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I myself would pay to paint in the city of Michelangelo.{\r}\N能在米开朗基罗的城市里作画 倒贴钱我都愿意
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.05,0:25:59.06,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Well, to each his own.{\r}\N也对 人各有志
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.44,0:26:01.38,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}This is the painting here, behind the drape.{\r}\N这就是那幅画 就在帘子后面
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.16,0:26:03.17,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Now, where's the priest?{\r}\N牧师们呢?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.98,0:26:08.66,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Father! We've come to see the Rubens.{\r}\N神父!我们来看鲁本斯的画作啦!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.31,0:26:11.75,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Does light hurt the painting?{\r}\N光线会伤到这幅画吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.93,0:26:14.30,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}On the contrary, young Robert.{\r}\N恰恰相反 罗伯特
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.94,0:26:16.87,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's light that brings a painting to life.{\r}\N正是光线给这幅画注入了生命
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.53,0:26:19.08,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}So why does he keep it covered?{\r}\N那为什么要把它遮住呢?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.65,0:26:21.87,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Let's just say, it wasn't Rubens' idea.{\r}\N这并不是鲁本斯的本意
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.58,0:26:24.85,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}His paintings were meant to be enjoyed by everyone.{\r}\N他的画作本来是应该让人人都有机会欣赏的
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.85,0:26:26.93,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}As if the masses were interested in art.{\r}\N说的就好像人人都对艺术感兴趣一样
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.25,0:26:29.04,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Father.{\r}\N神父
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.44,0:26:34.69,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Oh, yes{\r}\N噢 对了
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.40,0:26:38.51,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Robert, you surely have a silver franc.{\r}\N罗伯特 你应该有个银法郎吧
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.20,0:26:46.33,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Bless you.{\r}\N保佑你
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.15,0:26:58.68,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}This is the house of God!{\r}\N这里可是圣殿!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.98,0:27:06.18,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Patrasche, no! Come! - You!{\r}\N-帕奇 别这样!过来! -你!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.76,0:27:10.90,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- You thief! Thief! - Nello.{\r}\N-你这个小偷! 你这个贼! -尼洛
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.48,0:27:13.01,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Little sinner!{\r}\N你这罪人!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.01,0:27:15.76,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}If you worried so much about souls as you do silver...{\r}\N你要是像关心法郎一样关心苍生...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.76,0:27:18.33,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}there'd be no sinners in this city!{\r}\N就天下无贼了!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.27,0:27:25.27,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello, it's all right!{\r}\N尼洛 没事了!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.46,0:27:36.89,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Patrasche, I was going to see Rubens' greatest painting.{\r}\N帕奇 我本来能看到鲁本斯最伟大的画作的
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.73,0:27:41.78,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You found my darling dog.{\r}\N你找到我亲爱的小狗了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.74,0:27:48.96,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Your dog? I found him by the side of the road. He was almost dead.{\r}\N你的狗? 我是在路边发现他的 他当时都快死了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.96,0:27:51.78,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Either way, he is mine.{\r}\N谁管你怎么发现的 他是我的
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.36,0:27:54.57,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}He doesn't like you.{\r}\N可他不喜欢你
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.88,0:27:56.62,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}As long as he obeys me, boy.{\r}\N我只要他听我的命令 小子
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.52,0:27:59.36,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Now, one way or another...{\r}\N现在 不管怎样...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.16,0:28:02.88,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I am taking my animal back.{\r}\N我要把这畜生带回去
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.80,0:28:04.94,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Understand me, boy?{\r}\N懂了吗 小子?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.94,0:28:06.75,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You understand me?!{\r}\N还不快给我?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.75,0:28:08.62,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Run, Patrasche, run!{\r}\N快跑帕奇 快跑!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.73,0:28:27.62,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- You try to run from me? - Stop!{\r}\N-想从我手掌心里溜走? -住手!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.62,0:28:29.17,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- I'll teach you better than that! - No!{\r}\N-看我不打死你! -不要!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.71,0:28:31.30,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}This dog is mine!{\r}\N这狗是我的
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.68,0:28:33.17,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's my dog.{\r}\N我的狗!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.37,0:28:34.82,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You stole him from me!{\r}\N是你从我这里偷的!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.22,0:28:38.28,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Now, get away or I'll cut your damn heart out!{\r}\N现在 给我滚开 不然老子就把你的心挖出来!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.70,0:28:42.24,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}No, Patrasche is mine! You left him to die!{\r}\N不 帕奇是我的! 你当时把他打得半死就丢下了它!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.17,0:28:48.10,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You let that dog be! Leave him alone!Get behind me! Get back behind me!{\r}\N住手! 离开那条狗! 快到我身后来 我来保护你!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.10,0:28:50.02,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You want trouble, peddler? You've got it!{\r}\N你想惹麻烦吗 臭贩子? 你死定了!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.17,0:28:52.37,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Come on!{\r}\N来啊!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.69,0:28:56.18,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Are you insane?!{\r}\N你疯了吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.44,0:29:00.52,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello, are you all right?{\r}\N尼洛 你还好吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.32,0:29:03.35,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Look out!{\r}\N小心!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.33,0:29:37.28,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's over.{\r}\N没事了
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.18,0:29:39.06,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's done.{\r}\N都结束了
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.33,0:29:48.55,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello, come with me.{\r}\N尼洛 跟我来
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.05,0:29:59.95,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You're a brave dog, Patrasche.{\r}\N你真是条勇敢的狗 帕奇
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.95,0:30:01.60,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}When can I take my bandage off?{\r}\N我什么时候能把我的绷带拆下来?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.21,0:30:05.54,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Keep it on for a while. Keeps the dirt from the cut.{\r}\N你还是多带一会儿吧 保持创口的洁净
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.13,0:30:11.77,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Are you a great artist, sir?{\r}\N你是一个伟大的艺术家吗 先生?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.09,0:30:14.40,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I strive to be, Nello.{\r}\N我正为此而奋斗呢 尼洛
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.86,0:30:16.94,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But perhaps not.{\r}\N但也许终其一生也达不到
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.94,0:30:20.56,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I think you're great, sir.{\r}\N我觉得你很伟大 先生
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.07,0:30:23.20,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I thank you.{\r}\N谢谢你
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.13,0:30:30.02,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- But Rubens was the best, though, right? - Rubens was a genius.{\r}\N-尽管鲁本斯还是最棒的 对吗? -鲁本斯是个天才
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.33,0:30:34.48,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Is that greater than great? - Genius is a greatness...{\r}\N-意思是比伟大更伟大吗? -天才就是...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.82,0:30:36.52,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}that burns like an eternal flame.{\r}\N燃烧并绽放出永恒光焰的伟大
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.80,0:30:45.36,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}That's you. I like that one.{\r}\N这是你的肖像 我喜欢这个
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.91,0:30:47.10,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You have good taste.{\r}\N你的品味不错啊
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.43,0:30:51.62,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}A very gifted student drew that for me.{\r}\N这是一个非常有天赋的学生为我画的
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.97,0:30:54.00,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Did he become great?{\r}\N他有变得伟大吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.97,0:30:56.93,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}She could've been.{\r}\N她本来是可以的
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.50,0:31:02.07,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But as you know, Nello...{\r}\N但是你知道的 尼洛...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.56,0:31:05.69,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}in our society, no one lets you forget what station you're from.{\r}\N在我们的社会里 总有人提醒你你的身份地位
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.89,0:31:08.34,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Especially for a woman.{\r}\N尤其对一个女人来说
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.70,0:31:12.24,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}She was from a poor family.{\r}\N她出身贫寒
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.18,0:31:17.27,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}She was young.{\r}\N当时她还年轻
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.49,0:31:19.78,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I was foolish.{\r}\N我真蠢
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.22,0:31:22.40,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I let her get away.{\r}\N我就那样让她离开了
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.68,0:31:30.77,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Master La Grande? -Yes?{\r}\N-拉格兰德先生? -怎么了?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.09,0:31:34.16,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I have a friend, Aloise.{\r}\N我有一个好朋友 她叫阿洛伊斯
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.62,0:31:35.62,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}She models for me.{\r}\N她给我当模特
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.34,0:31:39.01,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Would you like to see her picture? - Of course.{\r}\N-你想看看我给她画的画吗? -当然
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.36,0:31:55.46,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- You drew this? - Is it any good?{\r}\N-是你画的? -画得还行吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.54,0:32:01.54,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's exceptional.{\r}\N画得非常漂亮
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.37,0:32:04.05,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Especially for a boy your age.{\r}\N尤其是对于你这么大的男孩子来说
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.79,0:32:09.16,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Perspective is off here and there, but that comes with study.{\r}\N这些地方还需要一些透视效果 但这需要学习
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.76,0:32:11.97,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Do you ever give lessons in exchange for work?{\r}\N我帮您干活 您能教我画画吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.84,0:32:16.26,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'd be so honored, but I'm off to Rome.{\r}\N我很乐意 但我马上要去罗马
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.07,0:32:20.08,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}What about your friend? Does she give lessons?{\r}\N那您的朋友呢? 她教课吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.41,0:32:23.51,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}She went away. I never saw her again.{\r}\N她走了 我再没见到过她
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.45,0:32:26.64,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But, anyway, you don't need lessons right now.{\r}\N但是现在你暂时还不需要上课
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.80,0:32:31.09,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}The main thing is to keep drawing from your heart the way you do.{\r}\N现在最重要的是你坚持用心画下去 按你自己的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.13,0:32:34.01,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}and examine, look at things.{\r}\N要去仔细观察事物
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.01,0:32:37.33,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}The greater part of drawing comes before you even touch the paper.{\r}\N绘画最重要的部分 是在你接触画纸之前
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.87,0:32:40.47,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Ask questions, find out what things are made of.{\r}\N探究疑问 找出事物是如何构成的
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.96,0:32:44.32,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Store information for the inner eye, the eye of the intuition.{\r}\N为内心的眼睛 直觉的眼睛去积累素材
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.67,0:32:48.37,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Is that how Rubens did it? I want to become like him.{\r}\N鲁本斯就是这样的吗? 我想像他一样
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.73,0:32:51.13,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}That's good. Always reach for the stars.{\r}\N很好 要尽力去达到更高的目标
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.49,0:32:53.66,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You could be great, Nello. Why not?{\r}\N你会成功的 尼洛 为什么不呢?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.45,0:32:55.85,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Do you believe you could be great?{\r}\N你相信自己会成功吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.82,0:32:58.58,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Maybe.{\r}\N也许吧
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.71,0:33:01.24,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Good.{\r}\N很好
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.17,0:33:41.09,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Slow down!{\r}\N停下来!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.11,0:33:43.19,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I don't believe this.{\r}\N真难以置信
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.86,0:33:48.54,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Aloise, we talked about you racing through the fields.{\r}\N阿洛伊斯 我们已经谈过不许你去田里骑马的事了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.54,0:33:50.32,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Besides there's work to be done.{\r}\N而且我们还有活儿要干
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.56,0:33:53.81,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello says when he's a great artist, I'll never have to push a cart again.{\r}\N尼洛说等他成了大画家 我就再也不用推手推车了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.81,0:33:55.08,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Down you get.{\r}\N下来
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.73,0:33:59.20,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Well, Most artists would be happy to settle for enough to eat.{\r}\N很多画家只要能吃饱就满足了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.20,0:34:00.48,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Did he tell you that too,uh?{\r}\N他没告诉你这个吧?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.63,0:34:05.09,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Peter Paul Rubens was great and rich. Nello knows all about him.{\r}\N彼得·保罗·鲁本斯就很伟大而且富有 尼洛很了解他
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.89,0:34:07.50,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello can't even read or write.{\r}\N尼洛甚至不识字
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.39,0:34:11.32,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}So I'll teach him, and he'll use me as his model to paint.{\r}\N所以我要教他认字 他会让我当他的模特
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.94,0:34:13.57,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}He's such a good artist, Papa.{\r}\N他是个很不错的画家 爸爸
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.89,0:34:16.02,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I don't want Nello filling your mind with any more nonsense.{\r}\N我不想尼洛再给你讲那些胡话
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.02,0:34:18.10,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And there's no more riding. You've got work to do.{\r}\N不许再骑马了 你有活儿要干
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.10,0:34:19.81,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello have to find another model.{\r}\N尼洛得再找个模特了
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.42,0:34:21.30,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Come on.{\r}\N过来
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.61,0:34:27.48,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Your father just wants what's best. All fathers do.{\r}\N你父亲只希望你好好的 天下所有父亲都是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.53,0:34:31.76,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Why doesn't he like Nello? - He likes Nello.{\r}\N-他为什么不喜欢尼洛? -他当然喜欢尼洛
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.61,0:34:35.22,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}He just remembers what it was like when he was poor.{\r}\N他只是忘不了那段穷苦日子
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.47,0:34:36.90,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}How hard life can be.{\r}\N那时生活有多艰难
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.99,0:34:39.89,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Money doesn't make people happy.{\r}\N可钱不一定能使人幸福
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.37,0:34:43.41,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello and his grandfather, they're poor and they're happy.{\r}\N尼洛和他爷爷 他们很穷 但是他们很幸福
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.88,0:34:47.15,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You are so smart.{\r}\N你真聪明
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.31,0:34:49.91,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I don't know who you take after.{\r}\N我都不知道你像谁了
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.18,0:34:54.90,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello will be great. I know he will.{\r}\N尼洛会成功的 我相信他
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.53,0:35:00.07,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Of course he will. He has you to believe in him.{\r}\N有你这么相信他 他当然会成功
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.62,0:35:08.21,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello? Is that you?{\r}\N尼洛? 是你吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.84,0:35:11.09,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Master La Grande.{\r}\N拉格兰德先生
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.63,0:35:13.65,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You're home.{\r}\N您回来了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.69,0:35:19.54,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Yes and no. I must return to Rome. - Oh{\r}\N-是 也不是 我还要回罗马 -哦
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.43,0:35:23.44,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But not for long. The bishop wants a smaller nose, that's all.{\r}\N但不会去很久 主教想让鼻子画得小一点儿 就这样
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.83,0:35:26.65,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But look at you. I barely recognized you.{\r}\N但是看看你 我甚至都没认出你
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.65,0:35:29.83,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Of course, I recognized your friend, Patrasche.{\r}\N当然 我认得你的朋友 帕奇
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.20,0:35:35.07,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And your model hasn't changed a bit. Master Rubens.{\r}\N而且你的偶像可一点儿也没变 鲁本斯大师
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.57,0:35:36.90,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But let's see.{\r}\N让我看看
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.31,0:35:39.42,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Let's see how you are doing.{\r}\N看看你画得怎么样
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.19,0:35:50.65,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Your eye has grown clear and your hand strong.{\r}\N你的眼光更敏锐 手法更强了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.62,0:35:53.28,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You've cared wisely for your talent.{\r}\N你很明智地发挥了你的天才
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.81,0:35:58.18,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Perhaps it's time to graduate to painting.{\r}\N也许是时候升级到油画了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.03,0:35:59.81,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Painting?{\r}\N油画?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.46,0:36:02.49,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Perhaps it's time.{\r}\N也许是时候了
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.52,0:36:16.70,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}This is for you as well. All prepared.{\r}\N这些也是给你的 都准备好了
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.50,0:36:19.73,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And the brushes.{\r}\N还有这些画笔
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.09,0:36:22.45,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You'll need many brushes.{\r}\N你需要很多画笔
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.64,0:36:31.75,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Those are all for me?{\r}\N这些都是给我的吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.80,0:36:35.73,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Tools of the trade for a fellow artist.{\r}\N这些工具能换来一位画家
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.38,0:36:37.50,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Early Christmas present.{\r}\N提前的圣诞礼物
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.65,0:36:42.17,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I've never seen so many beautiful things before.{\r}\N我从没见过这么多漂亮的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.37,0:36:45.49,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Those pigments are very strong. Here...{\r}\N这些颜料色泽非常浓 看这个...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.15,0:36:47.49,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}try one color at a time.{\r}\N一次试一种颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.58,0:36:50.17,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Place it next to other colors...{\r}\N把它放在别的颜色旁边
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.61,0:36:52.80,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}mix them, fall in love with the colors.{\r}\N将它们混合 爱上这些颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.06,0:36:55.54,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And then look at nature...{\r}\N然后观察大自然...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.38,0:36:57.74,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}and your surroundings.{\r}\N和你周围的景物
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.36,0:37:00.88,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}See how these colors are reflected.{\r}\N看看这些颜色是怎样的
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.23,0:37:03.30,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}How many colors, for instance, in your blouse?{\r}\N比如 你的上衣 有几种颜色?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.73,0:37:07.86,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Let's see. Blue, of course.{\r}\N我们来看看 有蓝色 肯定的
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.45,0:37:11.17,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}There's white.{\r}\N还有白色
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.41,0:37:13.60,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But it has other colors as well.{\r}\N但它也有其它的颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.08,0:37:21.04,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But, also, green will bring it to that shade exactly.{\r}\N但是 一点点绿色能让颜色看起来更接近
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.09,0:37:23.84,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Experiment.{\r}\N这只是个试验
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.01,0:37:25.41,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Here.{\r}\N拿着这个
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.46,0:37:30.32,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Sometimes at the end of a day I have 30 colors...{\r}\N有时候一天下来 我的调色板上会有30种颜色...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.96,0:37:33.41,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}in my palette, different shades.{\r}\N明暗各不相同
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.44,0:37:37.39,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Now for a box for you.{\r}\N现在我要送你一个盒子
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.07,0:37:42.68,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Nello. Nello? - What?{\r}\N-尼洛 尼洛? -怎么了?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.91,0:37:46.16,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}The city fathers...{\r}\N市里的神父们...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.93,0:37:50.44,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}sponsor a Rubens Junior Art Contest each Christmas.{\r}\N每个圣诞节会主办一个鲁本斯初级绘画比赛
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.71,0:37:52.58,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You must enter it.{\r}\N你必须参加
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.40,0:37:57.65,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I could never win.{\r}\N我赢不了的
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.68,0:38:00.48,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}What's that?{\r}\N你说什么?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.55,0:38:03.76,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Is that my pupil speaking?Um?{\r}\N这是我的学生说的话吗?嗯?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.00,0:38:06.97,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}How could I?{\r}\N我怎么能赢呢?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.57,0:38:10.60,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}The first step to winning is believing you could win.{\r}\N成功的第一步 就是相信你能赢
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.17,0:38:12.49,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Of course you can win, Nello.{\r}\N你当然能赢 尼洛
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.41,0:38:15.57,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's too late for me.{\r}\N已经太晚了
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.57,0:38:20.80,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}There's plenty of time before Christmas. You can do it.{\r}\N在圣诞之前你还有很多时间 你能行的
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.68,0:38:24.20,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I mean it's too late for me to start my art studies.{\r}\N我的意思是开始学画画已经太迟了
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.86,0:38:25.86,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nonsense.{\r}\N胡说
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.65,0:38:29.85,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Rubens himself was older than you when he started.{\r}\N鲁本斯开始学画画的时候年龄比你还大
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.74,0:38:32.02,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Really? - Really.{\r}\N-真的? -真的
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.54,0:38:34.08,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And did I forget to mention...{\r}\N我忘了告诉你...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.41,0:38:38.00,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}that the winner gets 1000 silver francs...{\r}\N胜者能拿到1000法郎奖金...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.56,0:38:40.32,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}and a scholarship to art school?{\r}\N还能拿到去艺术院校的奖学金
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.60,0:38:42.91,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Did you hear that, Patrasche?{\r}\N听见了吗 帕奇?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.39,0:38:48.69,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}One thousand silver francs.{\r}\N一千法郎
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.98,0:38:52.57,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And he's going to win it, Patrasche. He's going to win it.{\r}\N他会赢的 帕奇 他会赢的
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.13,0:39:04.43,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}-Hi Aloise. - Hi, Nello. I made you some cookies.{\r}\N-嗨 阿洛伊斯 -嗨 尼洛 我给你做了点饼干
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.80,0:39:08.29,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}They're not that good, though. Mother says I ride better than I cook.{\r}\N做得不太好 妈妈说我骑马比做饼干强
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.64,0:39:10.87,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Papa thought the heart-shaped cookie was for him.{\r}\N爸爸以为心形的饼干是给他的呢
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.68,0:39:13.23,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And this one's for Patrasche.{\r}\N这个是给帕奇的
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.25,0:39:16.49,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Thanks, but...{\r}\N谢谢你 但是...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.49,0:39:18.92,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}they're too pretty to eat.{\r}\N它们太漂亮了 我都舍不得吃了
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.88,0:39:21.43,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I've got something for you too.{\r}\N我也有东西要给你
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.02,0:39:29.44,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's beautiful.{\r}\N太美了
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.88,0:39:33.63,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- What is it? - It's what it will be that matters.{\r}\N-这是什么? -重要的是它将是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.22,0:39:37.31,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'll call it Portrait of a Princess.{\r}\N我把它叫做公主的画像
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.64,0:40:07.84,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's beautiful.{\r}\N太漂亮了
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.94,0:40:12.33,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I feel so small when I look up at the sky.{\r}\N当我看着天空的时候 我觉得自己是那么渺小
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.57,0:40:14.45,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Really?{\r}\N真的?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.99,0:40:18.33,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Why are some people born rich, some poor...{\r}\N为什么有些人生来就富有 有些却生来就贫穷...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.29,0:40:20.41,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}some healthy...{\r}\N有些人健康...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.78,0:40:22.93,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}some real sick?{\r}\N有些人却带着疾病?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.43,0:40:25.68,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It just isn't fair.{\r}\N这不公平
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.68,0:40:28.34,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I really hadn't thought much about that yet.{\r}\N我还没想过这些
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.50,0:40:34.05,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Ever since my mother died...{\r}\N妈妈去世以后...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.08,0:40:36.30,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I've wondered where she went.{\r}\N我一直在想她去了哪里
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.17,0:40:43.36,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Maybe she's one of those real bright stars that come out every night.{\r}\N也许她是夜空中那些闪耀着的明星中的一颗
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.40,0:40:45.52,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I hope so.{\r}\N希望是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.14,0:40:50.58,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It wouldn't be right if the spirit of a great man like Rubens...{\r}\N如果像鲁本斯那样的伟人 
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.12,0:40:54.17,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}and good people like my mother just didn't go on after they died.{\r}\N和我妈妈那样的好人死后没有灵魂的话... 那多遗憾啊
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.18,0:40:57.68,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'm sure you're right, Nello.{\r}\N我相信你是对的 尼洛
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.40,0:41:00.10,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}God's too smart for that.{\r}\N上帝对此很清楚
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.01,0:41:17.89,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- I'd better go. - It's time to go, Aloise.{\r}\N-我该走了 -该走了 阿洛伊斯
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.89,0:41:20.74,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Meet me here tomorrow night, and I'll finish your sketch.{\r}\N明天晚上在这儿见 我把你的画画完
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.74,0:41:21.97,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}All right, Nello.{\r}\N好的 尼洛
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.43,0:41:37.07,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You're going to be a great artist, just like Rubens.{\r}\N你一定会成为一个伟大的画家 就像鲁本斯一样
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.66,0:41:41.28,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Listen.{\r}\N听
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.71,0:41:44.51,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Can you hear it?{\r}\N你听见了吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.93,0:41:49.71,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Yes.{\r}\N听见了
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.44,0:41:52.03,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Music.{\r}\N有音乐
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.08,0:41:57.34,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's the circus.{\r}\N是马戏团的人
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.86,0:42:00.33,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I saw them pass earlier on the way to the city.{\r}\N我之前看见他们在去城里的路上
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.65,0:42:05.14,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Papa says circus people stuff little girls in sacks and sell them.{\r}\N爸爸说马戏团的人把小女孩装在麻袋里卖掉
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.66,0:42:07.11,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Like grain? That's silly.{\r}\N像卖粮食一样? 怎么可能
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.58,0:42:10.11,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}They travel and play games and make people happy.{\r}\N他们四处旅行 表演马戏 让人们开心的
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.69,0:42:11.83,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}How could they be bad?{\r}\N他们怎么能是坏人呢?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.40,0:42:13.39,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I don't know.{\r}\N我不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.17,0:42:17.07,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I better get you home first.{\r}\N我最好先把你送回家
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.11,0:42:23.31,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello Daas, if you're not afraid, I'm not afraid.{\r}\N尼洛·达斯 如果你不害怕 我就不害怕
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.85,0:43:10.49,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Maybe we should go back.{\r}\N也许我们应该回去
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.00,0:43:13.76,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Are you kidding? This is great.{\r}\N你在开玩笑吗? 这太好玩了
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.69,0:44:13.86,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Come on, Nello.{\r}\N来吧 尼洛
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.67,0:44:27.58,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You will be great one day, little one.{\r}\N有一天你会成为伟大的人 孩子
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.53,0:44:32.25,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Your life and love will touch many.{\r}\N你俩的生命和爱情会感动很多人
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.87,0:44:34.97,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Your stars are crossed.{\r}\N你们的星相相交
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.18,0:44:37.87,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Your hearts beat as one.{\r}\N你们的心跳相合
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.51,0:44:41.23,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You have known each other before.{\r}\N你们前生就认识了
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.04,0:44:48.09,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}In this life, you will finally find true happiness.{\r}\N这一生 你们最终会找到真正的幸福
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.68,0:46:27.13,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Aloise! Where are you? Can you hear me?{\r}\N阿洛伊斯! 你在哪儿? 听见我了吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.13,0:46:31.65,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Aloise! Answer me!{\r}\N阿洛伊斯! 回答我!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.27,0:46:48.16,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Oh, my God! Thank God you're all right. - I'm sorry, Papa. I fell asleep.{\r}\N-哦 上帝! 感谢上帝你没事 -对不起 爸爸 我睡着了
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.57,0:46:52.26,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Master Cogez, it was all my fault. I wanted to draw her picture.{\r}\N库格兹先生 都是我的错 我想给她画画
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.26,0:46:55.41,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Do you have any idea how worried we've been? Any idea at all?{\r}\N你知道我们有多担心吗? 你知道吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.54,0:46:59.34,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Papa, no. It was my fault. - I'll deal with you later.{\r}\N-爸爸 不 这都是我的错 -我回去再教训你
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.89,0:47:01.73,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You're thoughtless and irresponsible, Nello.{\r}\N你太轻率了 而且不负责任 尼洛
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.73,0:47:04.61,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Aloise is our life. I won't let you jeopardize that.{\r}\N阿洛伊斯是我们的命 我不会让你伤害她
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.61,0:47:06.03,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Do you understand me?{\r}\N明白吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.33,0:47:27.45,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Millie, take Aloise inside, please.{\r}\N米莉 带阿洛伊斯进去
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.01,0:47:31.40,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello, would you come here?{\r}\N尼洛 你能过来一下吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.46,0:47:43.93,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}That picture you did of Aloise.{\r}\N你画的阿洛伊斯的画像
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.66,0:47:46.41,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Personally I think the painting is foolish,{\r}\N我个人认为那幅画糟透了
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.41,0:47:48.49,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}but it does look like her, and my wife seems likes it.{\r}\N但看起来确实很像她 我妻子很喜欢
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.68,0:47:52.59,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'll buy it from you.{\r}\N我买了
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.72,0:47:56.68,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's not for sale.{\r}\N那幅画不卖
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.82,0:48:01.55,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}So be it.{\r}\N那好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.89,0:48:07.04,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Anna. Fetch the boy's picture. - Master Cogez.{\r}\N-安娜 把他的画拿来 -库格兹先生
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.02,0:48:09.49,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's a present.{\r}\N那是我送给阿洛伊斯的礼物
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.78,0:48:11.56,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello, I want you to stay away from my daughter.{\r}\N尼洛 我要你离我女儿远点儿
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.29,0:48:16.02,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- But Aloise is my friend. - You're not welcome here anymore.{\r}\N-但阿洛伊斯是我的朋友 -这里不欢迎你了
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.69,0:48:24.07,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Because of last night?{\r}\N因为昨晚吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.44,0:48:26.06,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}No.{\r}\N不
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.97,0:48:28.12,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Because it's for the best.{\r}\N因为这样最好
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.86,0:48:32.16,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Best for who, sir?{\r}\N为了谁好 先生?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.94,0:48:59.49,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I could've seen the Rubens with that silver franc.{\r}\N有了那枚银币我就能看到鲁本斯的画
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.17,0:49:04.70,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I couldn't sell her picture.{\r}\N但我不能卖那幅画
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.76,0:49:09.70,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}One day when we're great, Patrasche...{\r}\N等有一天我们成功了 帕奇
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.60,0:49:14.53,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Aloise's drawing will be worth its weight in silver.{\r}\N阿洛伊斯的那副肖像就会一纸千金
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.07,0:49:22.98,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Don't cry. I'll talk to him.{\r}\N别哭了 我会跟你爸爸谈谈
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.44,0:49:35.42,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You're right to be upset with them, but you've gone too far.{\r}\N你生他们的气我可以理解 但你过分了
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.42,0:49:36.56,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}She'll get over it.{\r}\N她会好的
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.12,0:49:40.10,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Nello's like a brother to her. - Brother? Anna, come on!{\r}\N-尼洛就像她的兄长 -兄长? 安娜 算了吧!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.10,0:49:43.10,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- You know where this is going. - What if it did come to pass{\r}\N-你知道事情会怎么发展 -就算是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.10,0:49:47.25,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}would that be so terrible? Nello is a fine, hardworking boy...{\r}\N有这么可怕吗? 尼洛是个很不错的 勤奋的男孩...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.25,0:49:48.03,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}He's an orphan.{\r}\N他是个孤儿
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.51,0:49:52.58,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}No girl can do better than to be happy.{\r}\N没有女孩不想幸福的
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.82,0:49:55.71,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Even if it means marrying a tinker's son, like you were.{\r}\N即使是嫁给一个修补匠的儿子 就像你过去那样
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.04,0:50:00.89,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I married you for love. I went against my father's wishes.{\r}\N我因为爱你才嫁给你 违抗我父亲的意愿
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.89,0:50:04.02,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And I didn't judge you because you were poor and had dreams.{\r}\N我并没有因为你贫穷得只剩梦想而嫌弃你
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.02,0:50:07.34,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}No, no. I had ambitions. This boy dreams of being an artist.{\r}\N不 不是的 我有雄心壮志 可这孩子只想成为一个画家
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.34,0:50:08.57,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}What kind of future is that?{\r}\N那有什么前途?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.93,0:50:11.32,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I turned your father's simple farm into a prosperous mill.{\r}\N我把你父亲简陋的农场变成了一个兴旺的磨坊
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.72,0:50:13.99,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Is it so wrong for a father to want more for his daughter?{\r}\N一个父亲 想给他的女儿更好的 难道错了吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.99,0:50:14.76,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}No.{\r}\N不是
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.76,0:50:20.61,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But this mill will provide for Aloise, always.{\r}\N但是这间磨坊会养活阿洛伊斯 一直会的
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.79,0:50:24.96,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You forget. I know what it's like to be poor.{\r}\N你忘了 我知道穷苦日子是什么样儿
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.65,0:50:33.64,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello.{\r}\N尼洛
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.87,0:50:38.09,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's Aloise's birthday soon.{\r}\N阿洛伊斯的生日快到了
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.85,0:50:40.17,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I made her something.{\r}\N我给她做了件东西
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.33,0:50:42.85,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'm not going this year.{\r}\N今年我不去了
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.17,0:50:51.53,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Master Cogez is a strong man...{\r}\N库格兹先生是个很强势的人...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.53,0:50:53.78,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}but you know there is good there.{\r}\N但是你该明白他也是个好人
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.86,0:50:58.91,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}He just wants the best for Aloise.{\r}\N他只是希望她女儿能过得好
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.43,0:51:09.42,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Master Cogez thinks that money is all that's important.{\r}\N库格兹先生认为有钱才是最重要的
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.90,0:51:14.24,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Poor, my boy.{\r}\N可怜啊 我的孩子
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.52,0:51:17.44,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Being poor is hard on you.{\r}\N贫穷让你过得很艰难
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.44,0:51:20.16,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}We've lots. We've Patrasche and each other.{\r}\N可我们拥有很多东西 我们有帕奇 还有彼此
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.67,0:51:22.40,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I don't care what he thinks.{\r}\N我不在乎库格兹怎么想
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.41,0:51:30.78,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}A little more food would not be disagreeable, though, would it?{\r}\N不过多一点吃的会更好吧 不是吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.61,0:51:39.77,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}One day we will all be with God and realize this was just a dream.{\r}\N总有一天 我们都会回到上帝那里 然后意识到这一切只是一个梦
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.37,0:51:43.29,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Just one big dream.{\r}\N一个很长很宏大的梦
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.68,0:51:45.73,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Sometimes good, sometimes bad.{\r}\N有时候好 有时候坏
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.44,0:51:50.16,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Will we really all be together again after we die?{\r}\N我们死后真的还会在一起吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.16,0:51:51.76,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Of course!{\r}\N当然!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.46,0:51:54.38,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Our real home is with God.{\r}\N我们真正的家 是在上帝那里
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.88,0:51:58.70,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And he will not be happy until we all come back to him.{\r}\N而且直到我们都回到他那儿 上帝才会高兴
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.06,0:52:13.85,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Then I will see Mother again? - Oh, yes, yes.{\r}\N-那我还能再见到妈妈吗? -能 当然能
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.30,0:52:16.40,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But remember:{\r}\N但要记住:
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.82,0:52:18.02,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}She's here now.{\r}\N她现在就在这里
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.70,0:52:21.19,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Always with you, even though you can't see her.{\r}\N即使你看不到她 她也一直在你身边
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.31,0:52:53.89,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Here she is, the birthday girl.{\r}\N她来了 寿星小丫头
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.98,0:53:19.11,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Thank you for the lovely gift for Aloise.{\r}\N谢谢你送阿洛伊斯的礼物
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.11,0:53:22.74,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And so then I threw the old fool out...{\r}\N然后我把那个愚蠢的老家伙扔了出去...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.96,0:53:24.54,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}and then I bought her house for nothing.{\r}\N然后没出钱就得到了她的房子
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.00,0:53:28.98,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Sir? - Thank you, Millie.{\r}\N-先生? -谢谢你 米莉
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.33,0:53:33.62,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Thank you.{\r}\N谢谢
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.49,0:53:42.43,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You look very beautiful tonight, Millie.{\r}\N米莉 你今晚看起来真美
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.98,0:53:47.12,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Olga, thank you very much for coming.{\r}\N奥尔加 谢谢你今晚能来
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.12,0:53:52.75,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Sweetheart, you go on ahead. I have business I want to discuss with Nicholas.{\r}\N亲爱的 你先走吧 我有事情要和尼古拉斯谈谈
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.08,0:53:55.65,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Business tonight? Discuss something tonight?{\r}\N谈事情? 今晚要谈事情?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.65,0:53:58.54,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I won't have my wits about me. Not after this much ale.{\r}\N今晚我可没什么脑子 尤其是喝了这么多酒之后
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.54,0:54:00.74,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Exactly, my friend! Exactly.{\r}\N当然要谈 我的朋友! 当然
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.47,0:54:04.49,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Because you are too sly for me when you are sober.{\r}\N因为对我来说你清醒的时候太滑头了
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.22,0:54:08.66,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You've had enough.{\r}\N够了 你喝多了
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.42,0:54:13.30,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I know when I have had enough.{\r}\N我知道自己什么时候才算喝多
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.12,0:54:17.64,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Don't you ever tell me how to do my business, woman!{\r}\N还轮不到你来告诉我该怎么做 娘儿们!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.20,0:54:19.92,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Now you go on home.{\r}\N现在你给我回家
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.48,0:55:04.05,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Aloise! Aloise!{\r}\N阿洛伊斯!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.59,0:55:18.50,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Happy birthday, Aloise.{\r}\N生日快乐 阿洛伊斯
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.96,0:55:19.78,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello!{\r}\N尼洛!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.81,0:55:24.50,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}How pretty. I love it.{\r}\N真漂亮 我喜欢
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.98,0:55:29.78,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- It's hard not seeing you anymore. - I know. For me too.{\r}\N-见不到你真难熬 -我知道 我也是
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.33,0:55:32.98,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}After the art contest, everything will be different.{\r}\N等美术大赛结束之后 一切就会不同了
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.57,0:55:35.86,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I pray every night for God to let you win.{\r}\N我每晚都向上帝祈祷让你赢得比赛
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.14,0:55:38.89,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Then I can't lose, Aloise.{\r}\N那我就不会输 阿洛伊斯
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.18,0:56:03.76,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Fire!{\r}\N着火啦!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.00,0:55:59.45,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Fire!{\r}\N着火啦!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.23,0:56:27.46,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Oh, dear God!{\r}\N哦 上帝啊!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.89,0:56:29.23,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Oh, dear God!{\r}\N我的天啊!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.06,0:56:32.21,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}The house and the barn could go next!{\r}\N过一会儿房子和马厩也会烧着的!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.20,0:56:39.84,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Everybody get in a line!{\r}\N大家站成一队!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.06,0:56:43.09,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Get to the stream! Get the buckets!{\r}\N去溪边! 拿桶来!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.09,0:56:46.32,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Millie, get the buckets! Get the buckets!{\r}\N米莉 快去拿桶! 快去!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.88,0:57:25.71,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Help! - I'm trying!{\r}\N-帮帮忙! -我正在努力!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.01,0:57:38.22,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Grandfather!{\r}\N爷爷!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.22,0:57:44.65,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}What are you doing?{\r}\N你在做什么?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.89,0:57:54.98,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}These old bones can still help a neighbor.{\r}\N这把老骨头还能给邻居帮点忙
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.84,0:57:58.91,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Someone!{\r}\N来人!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.30,0:58:00.58,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Someone!{\r}\N快来个人!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.45,0:58:10.26,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- I'm going to lose everything! - Someone!{\r}\N-我就要一无所有了! -快来人啊!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.26,0:58:12.77,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Stephens! Get on the pump!{\r}\N斯蒂芬斯 快去压水泵!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.25,0:58:50.08,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}More!{\r}\N再来!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.46,0:58:51.67,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}More!{\r}\N再来点!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.05,0:59:39.22,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Water? - Yes.{\r}\N-要喝点水吗? -好的
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.88,0:59:41.86,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Thank you, William.{\r}\N谢谢你 威廉
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.45,0:59:46.77,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I owe you, William. Without your help, we'd have lost the barn too.{\r}\N我欠你的 威廉 如果没有你 马厩也保不住
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.77,0:59:48.91,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Are you all right, Grandfather?{\r}\N你还好吗 爷爷?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.45,0:59:52.62,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}A little winded.{\r}\N有点气喘
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.65,0:59:57.86,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Don't you find it mysterious?{\r}\N你不觉得奇怪吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.86,1:00:00.67,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I looked. I found no broken lantern.{\r}\N我看过了 没有找到任何坏掉的油灯
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.67,1:00:05.46,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}How could fresh, stored grain burst into flames all by itself?{\r}\N刚储存起来的粮食怎么会自己着起火来呢?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.48,1:00:09.90,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You mean someone started the fire deliberately?{\r}\N你是说有人蓄意纵火?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.13,1:00:14.83,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Does anybody have any idea who may have visited here after Aloise's party?{\r}\N有人知道阿洛伊斯的生日宴会之后 有谁来过这里吗?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.46,1:00:18.21,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You always see the worst in things. Accidents happen.{\r}\N你总是把事情看得那么坏 意外总是有的
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.21,1:00:20.37,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}This was no accident.{\r}\N这不是意外
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.60,1:00:23.59,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Come here, boy.{\r}\N过来 孩子
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.65,1:00:25.57,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Come here!{\r}\N过来!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.33,1:00:31.95,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You were looking for revenge, weren't you, boy?{\r}\N你是在报复 对吗 小子?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.35,1:00:35.60,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}For Master Cogez not allowing you to see Aloise.{\r}\N因为库格兹先生不让你见阿洛伊斯
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.26,1:00:38.68,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Was Nello here last night?{\r}\N尼洛昨晚来过吗?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.06,1:00:44.00,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}What are you holding?{\r}\N你手里是什么?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.83,1:00:45.68,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Where did you get that?{\r}\N你从哪儿得来的?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.68,1:00:48.16,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Anna, where did she get that?{\r}\N安娜 她从哪儿拿的?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.28,1:00:50.88,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Did you see my daughter last night?{\r}\N昨晚你见我的女儿了吗?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.45,1:00:56.05,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I don't believe this. Are you responsible for this fire?{\r}\N简直难以置信 是你放的火?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.48,1:01:01.01,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Do you really think that Nello could do such a thing?{\r}\N你觉得尼洛会做这种事吗?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.01,1:01:04.65,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}People will go to any lengths for revenge.{\r}\N人为了报仇可以不择手段
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.65,1:01:06.59,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I was in bed when the fire started!{\r}\N着火的时候 我正睡在床上
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.59,1:01:10.43,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- You started the fire. - Nello could never have done such a thing.{\r}\N-就是你放的火 -尼洛绝不会做这样的事
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.79,1:01:13.17,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Wait a minute, Anna. Stephens is right.{\r}\N等等 安娜 斯蒂芬斯说得对
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.77,1:01:17.30,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}The boy started the fire because he was angry with me.{\r}\N就是他放的火 因为他恨我
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.45,1:01:21.00,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- I did not! - You're a liar! Nello Daas{\r}\N-我没有! -你这个骗子! 尼洛·达斯
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.91,1:01:26.30,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}On what grounds do you attack my grandson?{\r}\N你有什么证据指责他?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.22,1:01:32.53,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}A birthday present?{\r}\N一个生日礼物?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.30,1:01:36.21,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I brought the puppet, but that was all.{\r}\N我拿了木偶送给阿洛伊斯 但仅此而已
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.21,1:01:39.88,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Proof! There you have it! There is your proof.{\r}\N证据! 就是它! 这就是证据!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.97,1:01:49.02,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}But I didn't do it! I didn't start that fire!{\r}\N但我没有那么做! 我没有放火!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.42,1:01:50.72,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Please believe me!{\r}\N请相信我!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.02,1:02:18.82,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Nello!{\r}\N尼洛!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.24,1:02:24.05,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}No one will do business with me.{\r}\N没人要买我的牛奶
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.55,1:02:25.97,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I know, lad.{\r}\N我知道 小伙子
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.93,1:02:29.95,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Stephens' man was already here.He's taken over your milk run.{\r}\N斯蒂芬斯的人已经来过了 他已经接手你送牛奶的活儿了
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.06,1:02:33.56,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}So that's who's been doing my deliveries.{\r}\N原来是他抢了我的生意
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.58,1:02:37.94,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Listen, Nello, I have some chairs. You and Patrasche can deliver them for me.{\r}\N听着 尼洛 这有些椅子 你和帕奇帮我送一下吧
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.94,1:02:41.20,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'll give you money. Let's get rid of your cans. You can leave them here.{\r}\N我会给你钱的 拿下来这些罐子 你可以把它们放我这儿
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.20,1:02:43.01,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Why don't you ask Stephens' helper?{\r}\N你为什么不找斯蒂芬斯的帮手
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.55,1:02:44.50,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Well...{\r}\N这...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.08,1:02:47.60,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}since I decided to quit drinking milk this morning...{\r}\N自从我今天早晨把牛奶戒掉之后...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.60,1:02:49.54,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Stephens and I aren't on speaking terms.{\r}\N斯蒂芬斯和我连泛泛之交都算不上了
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.24,1:02:52.01,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Of course, we were never very close.{\r}\N当然 我们也从没未亲近过
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.36,1:02:53.19,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Come on.{\r}\N来吧
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.07,1:03:16.24,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Rosa!{\r}\N罗莎!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.89,1:03:18.95,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Rosa!{\r}\N罗莎!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.44,1:03:43.41,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}After your mother died, a part of your grandfather died too.{\r}\N在你母亲去世之后 你祖父的一部分生命也跟着枯萎了
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.12,1:03:45.30,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And some of me.{\r}\N我也一样
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.35,1:03:49.71,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Your mother was a very special person.{\r}\N你的母亲是一个非常特别的人
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.24,1:03:53.36,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}What was she like?{\r}\N她是什么样的人
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.78,1:03:56.06,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Always smiling.{\r}\N她总是面带微笑
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.93,1:03:59.72,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}A hard life. Devil knows what she had to smile about, but...{\r}\N生活艰辛 天知道她在笑什么 但是...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.72,1:04:02.72,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}oh, she could light up a room.{\r}\N她却能照亮一整个房间
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.71,1:04:07.01,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I wish I could have known her.{\r}\N我真希望我能了解她
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.08,1:04:11.80,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}If you know yourself, you know her.{\r}\N只要你了解你自己 你就了解她了
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.17,1:04:16.83,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}When I win the art contest...{\r}\N等我赢了美术大赛...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.89,1:04:19.87,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}everybody will know Nello Daas...{\r}\N所有人都将知道尼洛·达斯...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.67,1:04:21.90,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}son of Mary...{\r}\N玛丽的儿子...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.81,1:04:24.08,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}grandson of Jehan.{\r}\N约翰的孙子
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.67,1:04:26.50,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Everyone. - Everyone.{\r}\N-所有人都会 -对 所有人
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.07,1:04:31.62,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Grandpa left this to me.{\r}\N祖父留下了这个给我
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.27,1:04:39.55,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It's from your mother.{\r}\N是你母亲写的信
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.55,1:04:43.69,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}"Dearest Father:{\r}\N最最亲爱的父亲
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.93,1:04:49.44,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}How long I've wanted to write you but could not find the words.{\r}\N长久以来一直想给您写信却始终找不到恰当的言语
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.34,1:04:51.55,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I had to leave. "{\r}\N我必须要离开
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.42,1:04:54.00,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I hope you'll understand.{\r}\N我希望您能理解我
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.88,1:04:58.77,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I did not want to hurt you or cause anyone disgrace.{\r}\N我并不想伤害您或招致别人的羞辱
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.01,1:05:03.33,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}God has his reasons, of that I am sure.{\r}\N我相信 上帝自有他的理由
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.04,1:05:08.21,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}The birth of my son was the most joyful day of my life.{\r}\N我的儿子出生那天是我生命中最快乐的一天
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.65,1:05:12.50,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It proves to me that real happiness comes not from our possessions{\r}\N它向我证明了真正的幸福不是来自于财富
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.50,1:05:15.20,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}or our positions, but from within.{\r}\N或者地位 而是源于我们的内心
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.60,1:05:21.47,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Father, I so look forward to sitting with you again by the water...{\r}\N父亲 我是多么想和您再次坐在水边...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.47,1:05:25.73,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}watching the boats pass, with your beautiful grandson on your lap.{\r}\N将您漂亮的孙子放在您的腿上 看船只驶过
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.62,1:05:30.60,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I heard Anna had a daughter named Aloise.{\r}\N我听说安娜有个女儿 叫阿洛伊斯
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.30,1:05:32.82,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Please give them my love.{\r}\N请转达我对他们爱
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.27,1:05:38.79,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}"Did Nicholas Cogez start building his windmill?{\r}\N"尼古拉斯·库格兹开始建造他的风车了么?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.82,1:05:41.77,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Well, for now I must go.{\r}\N好啦 现在我必须走了
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.75,1:05:47.98,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Give everyone my very best wishes for a happy, healthy Christmas.{\r}\N祝每个人都有一个健康快乐的圣诞节
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.74,1:05:52.27,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Love always, your daughter, Mary.{\r}\N永远爱你的女儿 玛丽
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.73,1:05:56.61,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}P.S. His name is Nello. "{\r}\N附注 他的名字叫尼洛"
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.37,1:06:02.35,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Why not come back to the shop and have a bite?{\r}\N回商店吃点东西怎么样?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.66,1:06:03.80,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You could stay the night.{\r}\N你可以留下来过夜
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.60,1:06:09.05,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I could use the company.{\r}\N我有这个权利做主
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.09,1:06:13.74,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Thank you...{\r}\N谢谢你...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.74,1:06:18.50,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}but I've something very important to do.{\r}\N但我有非常重要的事情要去做
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.90,1:08:03.24,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Please, sir! Here's my painting for the Rubens Art Contest.{\r}\N你好 先生!这是我参加鲁本斯美术比赛的作品
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.24,1:08:06.59,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'm sorry, the deadline passed three minutes ago.{\r}\N非常抱歉 可是截止时间在三分钟前就到了
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.59,1:08:08.07,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}No, but I must win.{\r}\N不 我一定要赢
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.66,1:08:09.88,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Perhaps next year.{\r}\N等明年吧
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.58,1:08:13.33,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I have to win this year! It's my only hope.{\r}\N我今年一定要赢!这是我唯一的希望
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.33,1:08:15.87,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'm sorry. I'm late and my family is waiting.{\r}\N非常抱歉 我马上就要迟到了而且我的家人正在等我
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.58,1:08:17.49,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Please, sir.{\r}\N求求你了 先生
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.82,1:08:27.70,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}This is...{\r}\N这...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.21,1:08:30.08,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}very good.{\r}\N很漂亮
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.58,1:08:32.32,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}This is...{\r}\N这画...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.22,1:08:35.22,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}really good.{\r}\N棒极了
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.05,1:08:38.79,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I'll take it.{\r}\N我会交上去的
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.36,1:08:40.43,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Thank you, sir.{\r}\N太感谢了 先生
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.85,1:08:44.92,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- Merry Christmas. - Merry Christmas to you, sir.{\r}\N-圣诞快乐 -圣诞快乐 先生
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.92,1:08:45.62,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Good luck.{\r}\N祝你好运
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.57,1:08:49.93,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You're late again on the rent, boy.{\r}\N你又没有按时交租金 小子
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.26,1:08:52.21,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}How many times have I warned you?{\r}\N我警告过你多少次了?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.56,1:08:54.96,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I still have to pay off Grandfather's funeral.{\r}\N我得先付清爷爷的葬礼费用
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.96,1:08:58.08,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I am not interested in your troubles.{\r}\N我对你的问题不感兴趣
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.58,1:09:00.29,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You will have to leave.{\r}\N你必须得滚出去了
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.29,1:09:03.11,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}As for this month's, I'll settle for the dog.{\r}\N至于这个月的租金 就用这只狗来抵账
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.70,1:09:05.27,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}No! He's my best friend.{\r}\N不!他是我最好的朋友
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.51,1:09:09.66,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You can't afford to feed yourself.{\r}\N你连自己都养不活
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.16,1:09:12.93,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}When I win the art contest, we'll have all the money we need.{\r}\N等我赢了比赛 我就会有足够的钱了
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.54,1:09:16.58,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You are a dreamer, boy. Just like your mother.{\r}\N孩子 你跟你妈一样 只会做白日梦
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.58,1:09:18.34,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}My mother was a great woman.{\r}\N我的母亲是个伟大的女人
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.34,1:09:20.80,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Keep the dog. I'll take this.{\r}\N留着你的狗吧 我把这拿走了
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.61,1:09:22.24,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}No!{\r}\N不!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.24,1:09:27.27,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}And you leave me every miserable scrap that you own.{\r}\N把你这儿的东西都给我留下
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.27,1:09:30.02,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I want you out of here by the morning.{\r}\N我希望你在明早之前滚出这里
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.41,1:09:35.43,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}- But I've no place to go, sir. - You are not my responsibility!{\r}\N-但我没有地方可去 先生 -这不关我的事!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.81,1:09:39.51,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Don't blame me for your miserable life, boy.Blame your mother.{\r}\N不要把你的悲惨的生活赖到我身上 要怨就怨你的母亲
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.37,1:09:42.41,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Out of here by the morning.{\r}\N明早之前滚出去
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.86,1:10:10.56,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Can't you wait until after Christmasto rebuild?{\r}\N为什么不等过了圣诞节再重建?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.56,1:10:11.52,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I tell you why.{\r}\N我告诉你为什么
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.52,1:10:14.51,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Because with what we lost in the fire,I have to work the mill twice as much.{\r}\N因为大火带来的损失 我必须让磨坊加倍工作
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.51,1:10:16.57,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Besides, I have nowhere to store the grain.{\r}\N而且 粮食没有存放的地方了
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.54,1:10:21.17,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I should never have let you borrow on the farm to build that damn windmill.{\r}\N我真不该让你借钱去在农场建那该死的风车
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.31,1:10:25.91,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Really? Well, you like your city-bought party dresses well enough.{\r}\N是吗? 你不是很喜欢城里卖的礼服裙吗
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.89,1:10:31.46,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I liked our simple life.{\r}\N我喜欢我们简单的生活
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.96,1:10:34.64,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}I liked the man I married.{\r}\N我爱的是我嫁给的那个男人
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.18,1:10:39.31,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}You've become just like Stephens,driven by the money instead of your heart.{\r}\N你已经变得像斯蒂芬斯一样 被金钱所奴役而丧失了自我
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.24,1:10:42.64,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}My duty is to provide for my family.{\r}\N我的责任是养活我的家人
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.16,1:10:48.73,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It takes more than money to provide for your family, Nicholas.{\r}\N可是家人需要的是比金钱更重要的东西 尼古拉斯
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.32,1:11:52.93,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Welcome, ladies and gentlemen.{\r}\N女士们 先生们 欢迎大家
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.01,1:11:58.04,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Every Christmas, nothing gives me more pleasure...{\r}\N每一个圣诞节 没有任何事情...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.04,1:12:01.06,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Well, let's say, almost nothing...{\r}\N应该说是 几乎没有任何事情
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.21,1:12:08.43,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}than the Peter Paul Rubens Young People's Art Competition.{\r}\N比彼得·保罗·鲁本斯青年美术大赛更能带给我快乐
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.09,1:12:12.40,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}For without Rubens, what would our city be?{\r}\N要是没有鲁本斯我们的城市会是什么样子?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.68,1:12:15.12,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}It would be like a Christmas without...{\r}\N就如同圣诞节没有
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.12,1:12:19.52,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}...roasted pheasant, plum pudding,fine wine.{\r}\N烤鸡 葡萄干布丁 美酒
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.52,1:12:21.98,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Cold ale! Hail ale!{\r}\N冰啤酒! 啤酒万岁!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.38,1:12:29.03,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Moving right along, with our esteemed judges...{\r}\N下面 隆重介绍我们尊敬的裁判...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.03,1:12:31.89,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Masters Steerns, Van Wyck...{\r}\N斯蒂恩斯大师 范维克大师
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.18,1:12:35.84,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}and, rejoining our fair city after a long absence...{\r}\N还有 我们久违的...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.84,1:12:37.68,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Michel La Grande.{\r}\N米歇尔·拉格兰德
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.18,1:12:50.50,电影,,0,0,0,,{\fntimes New Roman\b1\fs21\3c&H000000&}Please, Master La Grande, say a few words and announce the winner, please.{\r}\N请拉格兰德先生大师并宣布获胜者 有请
